               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; first words (headings or parts of headings) of constituent texts; directives for the ministers; some of the musical notation signs above the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
The incipit parts of texts I, II, III are written alternately in red and black lines (s. fols. 3r, 26r, 40ra).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>-In Text IV-2) by beginning of the excerpt from the “Book of the Testament" (fol. 71vb) is not marked with the heading ʾƎm-mäṣḥafä kidan zä-nägäromu....</note>
                  </msItem>
